<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2948: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-29T17:00:00-04:00">June 29, 1948—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>950. Emb authorized reach agreement Chinese on basis recommended urtel
                            1178 June 29. Dept believes would be desirable obtain written assurances
                            re substance 3 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>), 3 (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                            and 3 (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) but will leave it your discretion what
                            assurances along these lines, written or oral, should be requested.
                            Should be made clear to Chinese that any written assurances agreed upon
                            will be made public.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>